Q.1>Write a Python program that prompts the user to enter three integers. Print the largest of the three integers.
Input Format:
The program will prompt the user to enter three integers, one per line.
Output Format:
The output will display the largest integer among the three integers.

Code-
num1 = int(input())
num2 = int(input())
num3 = int(input())
largest = max(num1, num2, num3)
print(largest)

Q.2>Write a Python program to convert temperature from Celsius to Fahrenheit.

Code-
celsius = float(input())
fahrenheit = (celsius * 9/5) + 32
print(f"{fahrenheit:.2f}")

